# Yagi-Uda Antenna Design

## Overview

This project presents the design and electromagnetic simulation of a **Yagi-Uda directional antenna** operating at **10.9 GHz** using **ANSYS HFSS**.

The objective was to design a directional antenna and evaluate its RF performance through electromagnetic simulation. Key performance metrics such as return loss (S11), VSWR, gain, directivity, and radiation pattern were analyzed to assess the antenna's suitability for high-frequency wireless communication applications.

## Objectives

- Design a Yagi-Uda antenna operating at **10.9 GHz**.
- Model and simulate the antenna using ANSYS HFSS.
- Analyze impedance matching through S11 and VSWR.
- Evaluate gain, directivity, and radiation characteristics.
- Document the design process and simulation results.

## Software Used

- ANSYS HFSS
- MATLAB (optional for post-processing)
- Git & GitHub

## Operating Frequency

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Operating Frequency | **10.9 GHz** |
| Simulation Type | Driven Modal |
| Units | Millimeters (mm) |

